          %a{:name => "profile"}
          .section
            %img{:src => "images/two-2.jpg"}
            %h1 Attorney Profile
            %p As the grandson of an educator who became the first principal of a desegregated high school in Texas and the grandson of a welder who moved his family to the United States and began his own business, George was instilled with the values of education, hard work, and determination. 
            %p George attended St. Mary's University in San Antonio, Texas, where he graduated with Honors and was one of fourteen graduating students to receive the Presidential Award. 
            %p George attended the University of Texas School of Law in Austin, Texas, where he graduated three years later.  During this time, George completed legal internships with Judge Fred Biery with the Federal District Court of the Western District of Texas and with Chief Justice Alma Lopez with the 4th Court of Appeals of Texas, in addition to two clerkships with private law firms.  After a clerkship with the Texas Attorney General's Office, George went on to serve as a Policy Analyst in the Texas Senate during the 79th Legislature.
            %p George then worked for a law firm defending corporations and insurance companies in personal injury cases throughout the state of Texas.  While he enjoyed the legal challenge and experience, George knew his heart was with representing those whose lives had been forever changed by the actions of others.  He became a trial lawyer for a personal injury law firm in San Antonio, where he represented victims and their families for five years.  During this time, George handled hundreds of cases against insurance companies and corporations throughout Texas. 
            %p The Law Offices of George Salinas was then created with a devotion to represent the needs of families and people who have suffered in some way because of the actions of others.  Today, George proudly represents people all over the state of Texas.
